VI. Another is that we term Erotick, as proceeding from love, which is either contracted from Philtres or Love potions; (and then there muſt be given,


1. Vomitories of the Root of Aſarum, together with Bezoarticks, Aqua Benedicta Rulandi;


2. Sudorificks, as for inſtance, Treacle water, Diaphoriticum in acute diſtempers; the Appropriate remedy is the Secundine powder, touching which ſee more in Hartman:) Or elſe from a Venereal luſtful appetite, & an over great abundance of the ſeed; then in this caſe we are to deal with thoſe things that allay and qualifie the Veneral heat, and extinguiſh or (at leaſt) diminiſh the ſeed. See more of this Nature in Ferrandus, in his peculiar tract.

